sentences.english: A year ago, those nightclubs were packed with revelers.
sentences.chinese: 一年以前，那些夜总会总是人满为患。

sentences.english: And the conditions in temporary relief (temporary relief) camps are over crowded and in sanitary ( insanitary ).
sentences.chinese: 临时救灾帐篷已经人满为患，卫生条件也让人担忧。

sentences.english: Maternity wards in Shanghai were overcrowded during the first few days of the lunar year.
sentences.chinese: 农历年的最初几天，上海的产科病房人满为患。

sentences.english: The gym was crowded to capacity, and the volume of noise made us unable to hear.
sentences.chinese: 体育馆人满为患，喧哗声让我们什么都听不见。

sentences.english: Some kids study in the corridors as the classes are overcrowded.
sentences.chinese: 教室人满为患，一些孩子只好在走廊上课。

sentences.english: The prisons are as over-crowded as the farmlands are empty.
sentences.chinese: 监狱里人满为患，而田地却无人耕种。

sentences.english: When I go to meet a friend by the pool at the Mandalay Bay, it's too crowded to find chairs.
sentences.chinese: 我去曼德拉湾见朋友，那里人满为患，座位都找不到。

sentences.english: The Barbie store is packed on weekends at the moment.
sentences.chinese: 芭比专卖店在周末的这个时候人满为患。

sentences.english: Yamagata Miyagi Prefectural to go to the bus stop, from yesterday overcrowded.
sentences.chinese: 宫城县厅前去往山形的巴士站，从昨天开始人满为患。

sentences.english: Along with thc development of the tourist trade, all of famous scenic spot rull oftourlist.
sentences.chinese: 随着旅游热的兴起，所有风景区人满为患。
